                <h2>What is Colon and Rectal Cancer ?</h2>
                <p class="lead"><b>Definition of Colon cancer:</b> Cancer that forms in the tissues of the colon (the longest part of the large intestine). Most colon cancers are adenocarcinomas (cancers that begin in cells that make and release mucus and other fluids).<br><b>Definition of Rectal cancer:</b> Cancer that forms in the tissues of the rectum (the last several inches of the large intestine closest to the anus). </p>
            </div> <br>
            
