                <h2>Treatment Techniques</h2>
                <p class="lead">The Colonrectal cancer can be treated by various treatment techniques depending on the stage of the cancer. <br /> </p>
                <p class="lead"><b><h3>Prescription</h3></b></p>
                <p class="lead">Cetuximab by injection, Irinotecan by injection, Leucovorin by injection, Oxaliplatin by injection (Eloxatin), Fluorouracil by injection (Adrucil), Capecitabine (Xeloda)</p>
                <p class="lead"><b><h3>Also common </h3></b></p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Chemotherapy regimen:</b> IFL-Bevacizumab regimen, FOLFIRI regimen, IFL regimen, XELOX regimen, FOLFIRI-Bevacizumab regimen </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Procedures:</b> Colectomy, Proctocolectomy, Bowel resection, Radiation therapy, External beam radiotherapy, Laparoscopic surgery, Lymphadenectomy, Neoadjuvant therapy </p>
                <p class="lead"><b><h3>Specialists </h3></b></p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Oncologist:</b> Specializes in cancer</p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Radiologist: </b> Uses images to diagnose and treat disease within the body. </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Gastroenterologist: </b> Focuses on the digestive system and its disorders. </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Pathologist: </b> Diagnoses disease by examining body cells, fluids, and tissues. </p>
                <p class="lead"><b>Surgeon: </b> Performs operations to treat disease. </p> <br> <br> <br> <br>
